1.Make sure the device battery is sufficient.
2.Make sure that the headphone jack of the mobile phone is in good condition and free of dust (the earphone is fine for listening to music).
3.Make sure the device is fully inserted into the headphone jack.
4.Make sure that the phone is set to ringtone mode, not silent mode, and the volume is turned up.
5.Make sure that the headphone jack adapter is from the original phone manufacturer.
6.Make sure that other music and video apps that occupy the sound channel are completely closed in the background of the phone.
7.Make sure the App microphone permission is turned on.
8.If none of the above suggestions resolve the issue, please try another mobile device.
